<title>USA: ForeFront to cut work force, sees charge.</title>
<headline>ForeFront to cut work force, sees charge.</headline>
<dateline>HOUSTON 1997-04-30</dateline>
<text>
<p>ForeFront Group Inc said Wednesday it would restructure, cutting its base of 217 employees by about 10 pct, and expects to recognize a one-time restructuring charge of $700,000 to $900,000 in the second quarter.</p>
<p>The company said it remains &quot;on course with our goal to achieve quarterly profitability in 1997.&quot;  </p>
<p>The restructuring will organize ForeFront into two product divisions:</p>
<p>* Technical Professional Products, based in Clearwater, Fla., which will develop, license and market software to Network Managers, Network Administrators, PC and Network Technicians, WebMasters, and WebManagers.</p>
<p>* Content Management Products, based in Palo Alto, Calif., which will develop and market ForeFront's desktop Internet productivity products.</p>
